NAIROBI, Feb. 5 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people were killed and 12 others injured in a road accident along a busy road in northwest Kenya's Turkana County on Saturday night, the police confirmed on Sunday. Turkana Central Sub-County Police Commander Lemmy Njiru said that the accident occurred at around 10 p.m. when a truck driver lost control of the vehicle while avoiding hitting a camel on the Lodwar-Kakuma highway. The investigation of the accident is underway. Kenya's road safety enforcers blame increased road fatalities on speeding and drunk driving.  â– 